The '''Kosrae fruit dove''' ('''''Ptilinopus hernsheimi'''''), is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Columbidae]] found on [[Kosrae]] in the [[Micronesian Islands]]. It was formerly considered as a subspecies of the [[crimson-crowned fruit dove]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical mangrove forests.

